<title>Contrast-O-Vision Bookmarklet</title>

{{> site_head}}

<main>
  <h1>Contrast-O-Vision Bookmarklet</h1>

  <section>
    <h2>Here it is ⬇</h2>

    <a href="{{bookmarklet}}">Contrast-O-Vision</a>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>How to Install</h2>

    <p>On most browsers, you can right-click/long-tap on it, then “Bookmark Link”. Or drag it to your bookmark toolbar or folder or whatever. Check out <a href="https://mreidsma.github.io/bookmarklets/installing.html">Matthew Reidsma’s detailed instructions</a> if you need more help.</p>

    <p>On mobile browsers, it’s a pain in the buttockular region. Try searching for instructions for your particular device/browser combo.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>It doesn’t work on <i>[some website]</i>!</h2>

    <p>If a site has a <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/CSP">Content Security Policy</a>, that can block bookmarklets. Notable examples include:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>Twitter</li>
      <li>GitHub</li>
      <li>medium.com <small>(which is especially annoying because their contrast <i><b>sucks</b></i>)</small></li>
    </ul>

    <p>I’ll make a Contrast-O-Vision browser extension for them someday, but for now, nothing can be done.</p>
  </section>
</main>
